</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Offers $750 million in subsidies to build new ethanol production plants.   </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"> Hehe, it just gets better and better. If this was a commercially viable industry, why don't those companies build these plants on their own?  </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"> Exactly. If ethanol gave off more energy than it took to make, it <span style="font-style: italic">could</span> become economically viable someday, but here are companies like ADM who will get huge paybacks to wallow in the pork
