Ok, let me rephrase.  Who says the GOVERNMENT owns the Gulf of Mexico?  Why doesn't the guy who finds a resource and installs improvements own it, just like homesteading?  You know, 'prove up the land, live there, and it's yours.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The "government" doesn't own the gulf of Mexico.  If you establish a homestead in international waters, it is up to you to secure it.  Most companies secure their holdings through cooperation from a already existing nation.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">No limiting liability. NO NO NO. You make something that is found to be harmful: You need to be destroyed as a company. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well, that would be fine it you actually had an objective, knowledgable authority to judge these things.  Unfortunately, the best we've got is th US Court system.  The whole MBTE thing, as has been pointed out, is a crock.  You would never know that from how the courts and the legislatures have handled it.  Big Agribusiness has a LOT of money to throw around.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Our court system is pretty good.  bloated with @#%$ as it sorts out how to do IP law etc but still good.  If it is not good enough I strongly urge you to look at public education as the ruination of good juries.  People had more sense of things when they farmed their own land and kept their own books.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">How about we sue the living crap out of the perpetrators? 50 Million people hsould be collecting judgemnts. That would prevent a repeat of 2003's blackout. 
