<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That's because no one is forced to use tobacco.  It's a personal choice, and it's not like the knowledge that putting smoke into your lungs is not healthy is new.  And before someone spouts off about second hand smoke: don't go into areas with it if it bothers you, and content yourself with the knowledge that you're taking in just as many carcinogens by walking around downtown.
<br />

<br />
As far as the entire ethanol thing: seriously, read up on this before going off about it being a net energy loser.  Overall it takes less oil, including growing the corn, to use a high ethanol blend gasoline than to just use normal gasoline, in terms of vehicles.  That's why South Dakota uses so much of it.  Ditto with Brazil.  Brazil exports the vast majority of their own oil and uses ethanol-blended gasoline instead.  They do just fine.
<br />

<br />
Fusion: yes.
<br />

